bottom:32px;"><div style=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;In=
ter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;=
line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Last Saturday morning, shortly after this email=
 landed in your
inbox, I rang up an old friend from L.A. who=E2=80=99d been deeply impacted=
 by the Palisades fire. I wanted to say hello and check in, see if there wa=
s any way I could help him and his family, or simply attempt to take his mi=
nd off the tragedy for a moment=E2=80=94perhaps even make him laugh. Remark=
ably, he was in good spirits=E2=80=94in some state of shock, of course, but=
 filled with gratitude that he had lost possessions and not loved ones.</p>=
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">Given his vortex of experiences across politics and the=
 entertainment industry, we naturally began talking about the broader cultu=
ral implications of the disaster. Recognizing that the fires had disproport=
ionately impacted some of the wealthiest real estate in Los Angeles, he off=
ered a biting and yet entirely shrewd observation: that so-called insurance=
 advocates were quickly becoming the new <em>Varsity Blues</em>-style colle=
ge counselors in Southern California. Indeed,
these for-hire pit bulls presaged many of the political, legal, and financi=
al battles that are looming around the corner as we enter the next chapter =
of the recovery.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">He has a point, after all. Mere days a=
fter the flames erupted, we were already seeing the fallout of their politi=
cization: L.A. mayor <strong>Karen Bass </strong>had inexplicably traveled =
to Ghana before the initial blaze, despite early
reports of historic wind events amid a particularly dry winter. Her erstwhi=
le foe, <strong>Rick Caruso</strong>, seems ready to run against her=E2=80=
=94if she can even make it to a campaign before getting recalled. Meanwhile=
, Governor <strong>Gavin Newsom </strong>was already ostensibly cognizant t=
hat federal aid would come with standard caveats of Trumpian politics, a ga=
me he=E2=80=99d played during Covid. And there were the implications for th=
e entertainment industry, the forthcoming Olympics, and the
multi-hundred-billion-dollar resurrection of one of the most prized patches=
 of soil on Earth. I mentioned to my pal a detail from my partner <strong>M=
arion Maneker</strong>=E2=80=99s excellent private email, Wall Power: Art i=
nsurance executives were already signaling that they were going to dig in r=
egarding the underwritten value of various works. There is no Kelley Blue B=
ook for fine art.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p =
style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Shortly after our chat,
I texted my partner <strong>Peter Hamby</strong>, one of the great politica=
l bards of our day, who had been narrating the horrors of the fire on his p=
odcast, <em>The Powers That Be</em>. In a brief exchange, I wondered if he =
could dig into these questions. Was Bass cooked? Were L.A. heavies furious =
at <strong>Jeffrey Katzenberg</strong>, late of <strong>Biden </strong>fund=
raising fame, for supporting her candidacy? Would Newsom be able to manage =
the twin responsibility of the recovery effort and
the negotiation with the White House? You get the idea.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"=
>On Monday, Peter finished his extraordinary story, <a href=3D"https://emai=
l.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVZWFrQk1NbWd4aEJ=
vc1JEUzByYz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvdGhlLWJsb29kLWlzLWluLXRoZS=
13YXRlci1mb3Ita2FyZW4tYmFzcy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPVRoZStCYWNrc3RvcnkrLStTVUJTQ=
1JJQkVSUyslMjgxJTJGMTglMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PVRoZStCYWNrc3Rvcnkr=
LStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxJTJGMTglMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN=
0aW9uXHUwMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZG=
E0MmFiZDEyYSIsImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MjA0M=
zI4N30/0756420c5dd55bcd8365e62da97dfda62e0926b4cf9220dc024e5115a8dd7b5e" st=
yle=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;"><em>The Blood Is in the Wa=
ter for Karen Bass</em></a>=E2=80=94truly one of the most exceptional piece=
s of journalism that Puck has ever published. The piece lyrically and defin=
itively answers
these questions, among others, while delicately capturing the outrage and h=
arrowing emotionality of the event. =E2=80=9CIf it is true that she left th=
e country on a Saturday after the warning came out, that is a dereliction o=
f duty,=E2=80=9D Endeavor C.E.O. <strong>Ari Emanuel</strong>, who donated =
to Bass=E2=80=99s 2022 campaign, told Peter. UTA super-agent <strong>Jay Su=
res</strong>, one of Caruso=E2=80=99s biggest donors, was even more adamant=
: =E2=80=9CTo me, it=E2=80=99s utter incompetence at the highest level with=
 the mayor=E2=80=99s office.
The fact that she was not here on standby and ready to go? It=E2=80=99s unf=
orgivable.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><=
p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Only a few days later, Peter collab=
orated with our partners <strong>Matt Belloni </strong>and <strong>John Hei=
lemann</strong>, two native Angelenos, on an equally breathtaking piece, <a=
 href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2Uktxcl=
JLZ0dVZWFrQk1NbWd4aEJvc1JEUzByYz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvaG93L=
Wxvcy1hbmdlbGVzLWNhbi1yZWNvdmVyLWZyb20tdGhlLWZpcmVzLWhvdy1ob2xseXdvb2QtY2Fu=
LWhlbHAvP3V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1UaGUrQmFja3N0b3J5Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjE=
4JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1UaGUrQmFja3N0b3J5Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJT=
I4MSUyRjE4JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb=
3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRl=
cm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwNDYzMzN9/1954a33227cd93=
e4591f9a24ccf2b1135540f5e06f309d7fdd7117ba97653a3f" style=3D"text-decoratio=
n:underline;color:#d40000;"><em>L.A.,
to Hell and Back</em></a>, which captures and hypothesizes on the role of t=
he fires in Hollywood and the White House in all their granularity. It=E2=
=80=99s a heart-pounding read, filled with stunning insights about our curr=
ent era of disinformation, tech bros, and the politicization of, well, <em>=
everything</em>. We were equally proud to publish it.</p><p style=3D"margin=
:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">This weekend, I=E2=
=80=99d suggest you turn your attention to either of these pieces, if not
both. They=E2=80=99ll offer you a vivid and concise understanding of how th=
is unfolding tragedy will impact every meaningful industry in our culture. =
And when you=E2=80=99re done, I hope you=E2=80=99ll consider making a donat=
ion to one of the many charities that are supporting the recovery. This is =
truly the story of our time=E2=80=94and, indeed, one of the defining ones o=
f our age=E2=80=94and precisely what you should expect to read about in Puc=
k.</p></div>
